{"lemma":"حاكَة","slug":"حاكَة","root":"ح.#.ك","root_slug":"ح-_-ك","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-_-ك","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8666","n8681"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D8%A7%D9%83%D9%8E%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8666","headword_ar":"حاكّهُ","root":"Hk","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHaAk~apN","text_ar":"مُحَاكَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, KL) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HikaAkN","text_ar":"حِكَاكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He emulated, rivalled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"imitated, him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[originally, I suppose,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in scratching,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (K, KL, TA;) the inf. n. being syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mubaAraApN","text_ar":"مُبَارَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;) or like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mubaAraApN","text_ar":"مُبَارَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAk~ Al$~ar~a","text_ar":"حاكّ الشَّرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He produced,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"effected,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brought to pass, evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mischief."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TK.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","S","K","KL"]},{"entry_id":"n8681","headword_ar":"حَاكَّةٌ","root":"Hk","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tooth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) thus called because it rubs, or grates, ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHuk~u","text_ar":"تَحُكُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) either its fellow or what one eats: an epithet in which the quality of a subst. predominates. (TA.) So in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA baqiyta fiY fiyhi HaAk~apN","text_ar":"مَا بَقِيتَ فِى فِيهِ حَاكَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There remained not in his mouth a tooth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) The Arabs also say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA fiyhi HaAk~apN walaA taA k~apN","text_ar":"مَا فِيهِ حَاكَّةٌ وَلَا تَا كَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is not in him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, a grinder"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DirosN","text_ar":"ضِرْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor a dog-tooth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-'Amr Ibn-El-'Alà, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K"]}]}}